# GitHub personal access token. Two options:
#
# 1. Classic PAT — needs the `repo` scope (full control of private repos).
#    https://github.com/settings/tokens — "Generate new token (classic)"
#
# 2. Fine-grained PAT — scoped to specific repos. Required permissions:
#      - Pull requests: Read and write   (for create_pull_request)
#      - Contents:      Read-only         (for get_pull_request, list_pull_requests)
#      - Checks:        Read-only         (for list_pull_request_checks)
#    https://github.com/settings/personal-access-tokens/new
#
# The MCP server reads this file at boot. .env is gitignored; .env.example
# (this file) is committed as the template.
GITHUB_TOKEN=
